#, no-wrap
msgid "Data file formatting recommendations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-checklists.adoc:64
msgid ""
"For ease in understanding, we may use the terms *field* in this guide to "
"refer to the Darwin Core set of terms in the taxonomic publishing profile to "
"which a users data will be mapped. For example, we will refer to the use of "
"the *dwc:scientificName field* when referring to the Darwin Core term, "
"*scientificName*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-checklists.adoc:66
msgid ""
"It is recommended to use tab or Comma-Separated-Values instead of custom "
"field delimiters and quotes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-checklists.adoc:67
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-sampling-event-data.adoc:60
msgid "Be careful and consistent with quotation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/best-practices-checklists.adoc:68
