#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing DwC-A using the IPT"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:110
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Assumption: Your data are already stored as a CSV/tab text file, or in one "
"of the supported relational database management systems (MySQL, PostgreSQL, "
"Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle, Sybase). Ideally, you are already using Darwin "
"Core terms as column names, although this is not required.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:112
msgid ""
"The https://www.gbif.org/ipt[Integrated Publishing Toolkit (IPT)] is GBIFs "
"flagship tool for publishing DwC-As."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:114
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/index.adoc:36
msgid ""
"The simplest way to begin using the IPT is to request a free account on a "
"xref:data-hosting-centres.adoc[trusted data hosting centre] allowing you to "
"manage your own datasets and publish them through GBIF.org without the "
"hassle of setting up and maintaining the IPT on your own server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:116
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/index.adoc:38
msgid ""
"Otherwise if want to setup your own instance of the IPT the "
"xref:getting-started.adoc[Getting Started Guide] is your entry point."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:118
msgid ""
"The IPT can be used to publish resource metadata, occurrence data, checklist "
"data, and sampling-event data. The guide xref:how-to-publish.adoc[How to "
"publish biodiversity data through GBIF.org] provides a simple set of "
"instructions how to do so."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:120
msgid ""
"The IPT outputs a DwC-A during publishing and supports automatic "
"registration in the GBIF network. See the "
"xref:manage-resources.adoc#_visibility[IPT User Manual] for further details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:121
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing DwC-A using GBIF Spreadsheet Templates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Assumption: The occurrence data, simple taxonomic data, or sampling-event "
"data to be published are not yet captured in digital format OR a simple "
"solution for creating a metadata document to describe a dataset is "
"desired.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:126
msgid ""
"GBIF provides a set of pre-configured Microsoft Excel spreadsheet files that "
"serve as templates for capturing occurrence data, checklist data, and "
"sampling-event data:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:128
msgid ""
"xref:checklist-data.adoc#_templates[Checklist data template]: suitable for "
"basic species checklists"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:129
msgid ""
"xref:occurrence-data.adoc#_templates[Occurrence data template]: suitable for "
"occurrence data (specimen, observation)"
msgstr ""

#. .  Resource metadata template: suitable for composing a metadata document - pending but imminent
#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:131
msgid ""
"xref:sampling-event-data.adoc#_templates[Sampling-event data template]: "
"suitable for sampling-event data"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:133
msgid "Each template provides inline help and instructions in the worksheets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:135
msgid ""
"To publish the data as a DwC-A, upload the templates to the IPT. Use the "
"IPT's built-in metadata editor to enter dataset metadata. The guide "
"howToPublish[How to publish biodiversity data through GBIF.org] provides a "
"simple set of instructions how to do so. If you require an account on an "
"IPT, it is highly recommended that you request an account on a "
"dataHostingCentres[trusted data hosting centre] located in your country."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publishing DwC-A manually"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Assumption: Data is already in a CSV/Tab text file, or in one of the "
"supported relational database management systems (MySQL, PostgreSQL, "
"Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle, Sybase). The publisher does not wish to host "
"an IPT instance but does have access to a web server.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:141
msgid ""
"DwC-As can be created without installing any dedicated software. These "
"instructions target data managers who are familiar with the dataset to be "
"published and are comfortable working with their data management system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:143
msgid "Below is a set of instructions on how to manually create a DwC-Archive:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:145
msgid ""
"Unless the data are already stored in a CSV/Tab text file, the publisher "
"needs to prepare a text file(s) from the source. If the data are stored in a "
"database, generate an output of delimited text from the source database into "
"an outfile. Most database management systems support this process; an "
"example is given in the Annex to this guide, below, in the section "
"Outputting Data From a MySQL Database Into a Textfile. As the metafile "
"maps the columns of the text file to Darwin Core terms, it is not necessary "
"to use Darwin Core terms as column header in the resultant text file, though "
"it may help to reduce errors. A general recommendation is to produce a "
"single core data file and a single file for each extension if the intention "
"is to output data tied to an extension."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:146
msgid "Create a Metafile: There are three different ways to generate the file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:147
msgid ""
"Create it manually by using an XML editor and using a sample metafile as a "
"guiding example. A complete description of the metafile format can be found "
"in the http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/guides/text/index.htm[Darwin Core Text "
"Guide]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:148
msgid "{blank}"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "figures/dwc-a_assistant.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:154
msgid ""
"Create it using the online application "
"http://tools.gbif.org/dwca-assistant/[Darwin Core Archive Assistant] Simply "
"select the fields of data to be published, provide some details about the "
"files and save the resultant XML. This only needs to be done once unless the "
"set of published fields changes at some later time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:156
msgid ""
"this tool is no longer supported by GBIF. Support for the Event core is "
"missing. Publishers also need to manually add term dwc:taxonID to Taxon core "
"and dwc:occurrenceID to Occurrence core, to ensure they are explicitly "
"included."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:159
msgid ""
"Create a metadata file (eml.xml) that describes the data resource. Complete "
"instructions on doing this are available in the "
"xref:gbif-metadata-profile.adoc[GBIF Extended Metadata Profile: How-To "
"Guide]. It is best practice to include a metadata file and the simplest way "
"to produce one is using the IPT's built-in metadata editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:160
msgid ""
"Ensure the data files, the metafile (meta.xml) and metadata file (eml.xml) "
"are in the same directory or folder. Compress the folder using one of the "
"support compression formats. The result is a DwC-A."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/dwca-guide.adoc:162
msgid ""
"Metadata authored using IPT can be output as an RTF document, which can then "
"be submitted as Data Paper manuscript to Zookeys, PhytoKeys and "
"BioRisks. See instructions to authors for Data Paper submission to these "
"journals."
msgstr ""

