#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. What is the best way to move my IPT to another server without losing any "
"data?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:10
msgid ""
"There is one important directory that contains all the IPT's configuration "
"and resources: the IPT's data directory. If you ensure this directory is "
"regularly backed-up somewhere safe, you'll never lose any data."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:12
msgid ""
"To move the IPT to a different server, just make sure that you copy the "
"entire contents of the IPT's data directory over to the new server. It is "
"important to preserve the same folder/file permissions. Then, "
"xref:installation.adoc[install the IPT on the new server], using this "
"directory as the data directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid "2. My GBIF IPT instance is slow. What can I do to improve performance?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:16
msgid ""
"Apache Tomcat comes with very little allocated memory. In order to increase "
"performance, this amount should be increased depending on the amount of "
"physical memory on the server. If the server has at least 2GB of RAM, the "
"available memory should be increased to 1GB. For more information on how to "
"do it, see the http://wiki.apache.org/tomcat/FAQ/Memory[Tomcat FAQ]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:18
msgid "The following is known to run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"export CATALINA_OPTS=\"-Xms512M -Xmx1024M -XX:PermSize=512M "
"-XX:MaxPermSize=1024M\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"4. I get the following error: \"The data directory '/directory' is not "
"writable. What should I do?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:26
msgid ""
"Assuming you are running Tomcat, you need to ensure the user running Tomcat "
"has permissions on the directory. To find out the user running Tomcat on "
"Linux, open a shell and enter the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ ps waux | grep tomcat\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:32
msgid ""
"If the user is \"tomcatuser\", and this user belongs to group "
"\"tomcatgroup\" then change the ownership of the IPT data directory (and its "
"child folders and files) by entering the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ chown -R tomcatuser:tomcatgroup directory/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:38
msgid "To ensure only this user has write permission, enter the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ chmod -R 755 directory/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:44
msgid ""
"On systems with security sandboxing, you may need to grant permissions to "
"the directory.  For example, on Debian you need to add a SystemD override:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ systemctl edit syslog.service\n"
"[Service]\n"
"ReadWritePaths=/path/to/directory/\n"
"$ systemctl daemon-reload\n"
"$ systemctl restart tomcat8\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:54
msgid ""
"Note that if you are running your IPT on a windows operating system, you "
"will need to check that your folder didn't revert to read-only permissions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "5. How can I change the IPT's default language?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:58
msgid ""
"The IPT's default language is English, and there is no way to change the "
"default language via the user interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:60
msgid ""
"It can be changed easily by manual configuration though. To change the "
"default language from English to Portuguese for example, first locate the "
"struts.properties file (if the IPT is deployed in Tomcat for example, it "
"would be located in /tomcat/webapps/ipt/WEB-INF/classes). Then update the "
"struts.locale property to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:62
msgid "struts.locale=pt"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:64
msgid "Restart Tomcat, and the IPT will startup in Portuguese."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:66
msgid ""
"Please note the two-letter language code must match the code used by the "
"IPT. Other languages currently supported include Japanese (ja), French (fr), "
"Spanish (es), Traditional Chinese (zh), and Russian (ru)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:68
msgid ""
"Please note that every time you upgrade to a new version of the IPT, you "
"will have to apply the same change."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:69
#, no-wrap
msgid "6. How can I switch the IPT from test mode to production mode?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:72
msgid ""
"Switching the IPT from test mode to production mode cannot be done "
"automatically. This is by design, because each mode connects to a different "
"registry (test mode uses the GBIF Sandbox Registry while production mode "
"uses the GBIF Live Registry)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:74
msgid ""
"Therefore to switch to production mode you need to setup an entirely new IPT "
"instance in production mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:76
msgid ""
"To save time recreating resources, you can try transferring your 'test' "
"resources to the production IPT. To do this simply \"upload an existing IPT "
"resource using its zipped resource configuration folder.\" There are "
"complete instructions on how to do this "
"xref:manage-resources.adoc#_upload_a_zipped_ipt_resource_configuration_folder[here]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:77
#, no-wrap
msgid "7. What outgoing connections does the IPT make?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:80
msgid ""
"During setup, and in test mode, the IPT makes secure HTTPS outgoing "
"connections to https://gbrds.gbif-uat.org and https://tools.gbif.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:82
msgid ""
"If configured in production mode, the IPT makes secure HTTPS outgoing "
"connections to https://gbrds.gbif.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:84
msgid ""
"In both modes, the IPT makes normal HTTP outgoing connections to "
"http://rs.gbif.org.  If you install particular additional vocabularies, the "
"IPT will retrieve them from raw.githubusercontent.com or eol.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:86
msgid ""
"We recommend configuring your firewall to allow outbound access on ports 80 "
"and 443 to all GBIF servers: `130.225.43.0/24`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:88
msgid ""
"Before version 2.3.4, connections were made using HTTP, rather than HTTPS, "
"to http://gbrds.gbif.org and http://gbrdsdev.gbif.org.  HTTP connections use "
"port 80."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "8. How can I configure my IPT to assign DOIs to datasets?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:92
msgid ""
"In order to assign DOIs to datasets, the IPT must be configured with a "
"DataCite account, which has itself been configured to mint DOIs under the "
"IPT's domain."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:94
msgid ""
"The account holding organization must already be associated to the IPT as an "
"organization. For help associating an organization to your IPT, you can "
"refer to the xref:administration.adoc#_add_organization[Add Organization] "
"section of the User Manual."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:96
msgid ""
"All that remains, is to add the DataCite account information to the "
"organization (e.g. the username, password, prefix, etc) and make sure the "
"\"Account activated\" checklist has been checked. For help editing the "
"organization and a description of each field in the form, you can refer to "
"the xref:administration.adoc#_edit_organization[Edit Organization] section "
"of the User Manual."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:98
msgid ""
"If you work for a GBIF country' Node, please contact the "
"mailto:helpdesk@gbif.org[GBIF Helpdesk] to enquire about getting a free "
"DataCite account. GBIF has its own account with DataCite and may be able to "
"provide 'country' Nodes with their own free account (determined on a case by "
"case basis). GBIF has done this for Spain and Colombia so far, both of which "
"have a strong track record of keeping their IPTs online near 100% of the "
"time."
msgstr ""

