#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "1. How long does it take GBIF to start (re)indexing my dataset?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:213
msgid ""
"The answer depends on how long GBIF's indexing queue is, how big your "
"dataset it and whether GBIF's indexing service is turned on."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:215
msgid ""
"Normally it will take between 5-60 minutes for GBIF to start indexing your "
"dataset. It can take several hours to finish indexing large datasets once "
"started (e.g. with several million records) so please be patient. At the "
"bottom of the https://www.gbif.org/health[GBIF health page] the length of "
"the indexing queue is shown, and the full queue can be seen on the "
"https://registry.gbif.org/monitoring/running-crawls[Crawl Monitor]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:217
msgid ""
"If you believe GBIF failed to index your dataset successfully, please submit "
"feedback directly via GBIF.org, or send an email to the GBIF Helpdesk "
"<helpdesk@gbif.org> to investigate what happened. If you are interested in "
"finding out why GBIF may not have (re)indexed your dataset, please see 2 "
"below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "2. Why hasn't GBIF (re)indexed my dataset yet?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:221
msgid ""
"Occasionally, GBIF turns off its indexing service for maintenance (see the "
"links in the previous question). This is the most common reason why datasets "
"aren't indexed as quickly as expected."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:223
msgid ""
"If you believe GBIF failed to index your dataset, please submit feedback "
"directly via GBIF.org, or send an email directly to the GBIF Helpdesk "
"<helpdesk@gbif.org> to investigate what happened."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:224
#, no-wrap
msgid "3. How often does GBIF reindex my dataset?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:227
msgid ""
"GBIF automatically attempts to reindex a registered dataset each time its "
"registration is updated. This happens each time the dataset gets republished "
"via the IPT."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:229
msgid ""
"To cater to datasets not published using the IPT, GBIF automatically "
"attempts to reindex all registered datasets every 7 days."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:231
msgid ""
"GBIF will only reindex a dataset if its last published date has changed "
"since the last time it was indexed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "4. What type of datasets does GBIF index/support?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:235
msgid ""
"GBIF supports 4 classes of datasets described "
"xref:how-to-publish.adoc[here]. GBIF currently only indexes species "
"occurrence records though, which can be provided as either core records or "
"as extension records. In the case of sampling-event datasets, species "
"occurrences in extension records will be augmented with information coming "
"from its core event record wherever possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:236
#, no-wrap
msgid "5. Why is my dataset citation different on GBIF.org?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/faq.adoc:238
msgid ""
"The IPT supports free-text dataset citations, however, these get overwritten "
"on the GBIF.org dataset page. You can find out why in the "
"https://www.gbif.org/faq?q=citation[GBIF.org FAQ]."
