#. type: Title =
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Glossary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Checklist Resource* - a resource having information about one of many types "
"of taxon-related lists.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:4
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Core Type* - a category of predefined sets of data properties (Taxon, "
"Occurrence, and Event) used as the basis of a resource. Additional "
"extensions might be linked to these Core Types when mapping data in the "
"IPT.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:5
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*CSV file* - a text file that contains data in the Comma-separated Value "
"format.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Data directory* - the full (rather than relative) path (location) in the "
"file structure where the data associated with the IPT instance are "
"located.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Darwin Core* - a standard consisting of terms and classes of terms used to "
"share biodiversity data.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Darwin Core Archive* - a single zipped archive for a data set consisting of "
"one or more text files of data, an XML file (meta.xml) describing the "
"contents of the text files and how they relate to each other, and an XML "
"file (eml.xml) containing the metadata in EML about the data set.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*EML* - the Ecological Markup Language is an XML-based profile used to "
"encode metadata about a data set.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Extension* - in this user manual, an extension is a set of terms "
"corresponding to a specific category of data. An extension should be thought "
"of as an extension of the capabilities of the IPT rather than as an "
"extension of any particular standard.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*GBIF Registry* - a registry that manages the nodes, organizations, "
"resources, and IPT installations registered with GBIF, making them "
"discoverable and interoperable.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Metadata* - in this user manual, metadata refers to the information about a "
"data set as opposed the primary data in the data set.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:13
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Metadata Resource* - a resource having information about a data set, but "
"without having the actual primary data. A metadata resource might give "
"information about a collection that has not yet been digitized, for "
"example.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Occurrence Resource* - a resource having information about Occurrences as "
"defined in the Darwin Core.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Private* - a state of a resource in which only the creator, invited "
"managers, and IPT administrators can view it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Public* - a state of a resource in which anyone can view it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Published Release* - a version of the resource that has been produced by "
"the IPT.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Registered* - a state of a public resource or of an IPT instance in which "
"anyone can discover it through the GBIF Registry.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Resource* - in this user manual, resource refers to a data set and the "
"metadata about it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Resource Managers* - IPT users having a role that allows them to create, "
"change, and remove resources.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*RowType* - the category of information represented in an extension. The "
"RowType is generally the URI of the Class that best fits the information "
"contained in the extension.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*RSS* - the acronym for Really Simple Syndication, a type of subscription "
"format for tracking changes to a web site.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Sampling Event Resource* - A resource where the basis of the resource is "
"sampling events as defined in the Darwin Core.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Shortname* - a short unique name used for resource identification within "
"the IPT and services that access the IPT.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Source Data* - in this user manual, the source data are the data that are "
"mapped to core types and extensions within a resource and may consist of "
"text files or a database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/glossary.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Visibility* - a term describing how a resource may be viewed (private, "
"public, or registered).\n"
msgstr ""

