#. type: Title =
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Dataset Versioning Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:4
msgid ""
"The IPT carefully tracks the major and minor version changes for a dataset "
"so that each published version can be unambiguously identified, and users "
"can easily see when significant changes to the dataset occurred. The "
"relationship between all versions is visible in the version history table "
"(on its homepage) and also gets documented in the DOI metadata."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:6
msgid ""
"The versioning policy that the IPT uses is described below. It is important "
"to note that the IPTs versioning policy is based on "
"http://schema.datacite.org/[DataCite's recommendations], which are based on "
"the work of the "
"http://wiki.esipfed.org/index.php/Interagency_Data_Stewardship/Citations/provider_guidelines#Note_on_Versioning_and_Locators[Earth "
"Science Information Partners (ESIP)]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "Versioning Policy"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:10
msgid "Major and minor versions are used to track a dataset's changes through time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:11
msgid "The version number uses the syntax major_version.minor_version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:12
msgid ""
"A new major version is assigned to the dataset (a) the first time its "
"published, or (b) after it has been republished following one or more "
"scientifically significant changes to the dataset. The publisher must decide "
"what constitutes a scientifically significant change (see definition below "
"for help)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:13
msgid ""
"A scientifically significant change (a) typically affects the majority of "
"records in the dataset, and (b) could change the results of a scientific "
"analysis using the dataset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:14
msgid ""
"A new major version leads to the creation of a new DOI, whereas a new minor "
"version does not."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:15
msgid ""
"A new minor version is assigned to the dataset every time the dataset is "
"published, and it isnt appropriate to assign it a new major version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:16
msgid ""
"For continuously updated datasets (e.g. time series datasets), a new minor "
"version is assigned to the dataset each time it is republished, so long as "
"ongoing additions dont change pre-existing records in a scientifically "
"significant way. This decision must be made by the publisher."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:17
msgid ""
"A detailed summary of what has changed since the last publication should "
"ideally be entered by the publisher before any new major or minor version of "
"the dataset can be published."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:18
msgid ""
"Every major and minor version of a dataset has its own IPT landing page, "
"making the archived version of the dataset (DwC-A, EML) freely available for "
"download. Of course only landing pages of publicly available versions will "
"be freely accessible on the Internet."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:19
msgid ""
"All IPT landing pages will comprise a comprehensive metadata record "
"describing the datasets, and provide direct access to the data or "
"information about how to access it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:20
msgid ""
"The landing page of the old major version points (has a link) to the new "
"version, with an explanation of the status of the old version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:21
msgid ""
"Deleted datasets have an IPT landing page that explains the dataset was "
"removed. It the deleted dataset was assigned a DOI, all its versions are "
"archived otherwise its permanently deleted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:22
msgid ""
"The DOI metadata should be as rich as possible, including where possible (a) "
"alternate identifiers for the dataset, (b) relationships to other versions, "
"(c) relationships to articles the dataset cites, (d) ORCID where contacts "
"are listed, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/modules/ROOT/pages/versioning.adoc:22
msgid ""
"The dataset citation, should always include the version number, replacing "
"the need to use an Access Date and Time for citing time series datasets, for "
"example."
msgstr ""
